HEADWORD: Acutorsion
<hw>Ac`u*tor"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acus</ets> needle + <ets>torsion</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>The twisting of an artery with a needle to arrest hemorrhage.</def>
<note>[Not in Stedman -- an obsolete
procedure?]</note><mark>[archaic]</mark> <ver>AS</ver>⟦br⟧
